parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: (primarily physical), I look, see, perceive, discern. A primary verb; to look at.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.
Unbelief, unfaithfulness, distrust. From apistos; faithlessness, i.e. disbelief, or unfaithfulness.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (a) I am powerful, have (the) power, (b) I am able, I can. Of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible.
To go in, come in, enter. From eis and erchomai; to enter.
